{
  "action_id": "1807",
  "action_title": "Reprofile/relandscape peatland (without planting)",
  "key_messages": "Key Messages:\n\nOne study evaluated the effects of reprofiling/relandscaping peatlands (without planting) on peatland vegetation. The study was in degraded bogs (being restored as fens).\nPlant community composition (1 study): One site comparison study in Canada\u00a0reported that after five years, reprofiled (and rewetted) bogs contained a different plant community to nearby natural fens.\nVegetation cover (1 study): The same study reported that after five years, reprofiled (and rewetted) bogs had lower vegetation cover (Sphagnum moss, other moss and vascular plants) than nearby natural fens."
}

